Steps 7 & 8: Assign Labor Resources, Forecast & Shift Hours
Select to Click on the Handle Next to a WBS Line
Select Employee from the Labor Tab Toolbar
Select the Employee for this WBS Line
Select the Delete Button
Select to Click on the Generic Button on the Toolbar
Hold the Ctrl Key + Select Even More Generic Resources for this WBS Line
Right Click in the Handle Next to the WBS Line in the Plan
Select the Resource Search Menu Choice
Select the Generic Resource Tab
Select the Named Resource Tab
Select the Skill Drop Down Arrow
Select the Desired Skill
Select the Skill Level Drop Down Arrow
Select the Skill Level Desired
Select to Check On or Off if this Skill Level is Required
Select the Search Button
Select an Employee from the Resulting List
Select to Click in the Planned Hrs Column for the Phase
Press Tab key
Press Tab key
Select the Planned Hrs Row for this Resource and the Beginning Time Period
Right Click In This Cell
Select “Fill” From the Menu
Select the Drop Down Arrow
Select the Ending Time Period
Select to Enter the Hours/Bus. Day to Fill
Right Click to Display the Menu
Select the Spread Copy Menu Choice
Select the Down Arrow
Select the Ending Time Period
Right Click to Display the Menu Choices
Select Spread Evenly
Select the Ending Time Period
Select to Enter the Total Hours to Spread
Select Spread Proportionally
Select to Click in the Handle to the Left of this Phase
Select to Click on the Shift Button on the Toolbar
Select the Checkbox and Click On to Shift All Data on All Tabs
Select Input Capture Window
Select the Data to Shift These Labor Hours Forward To
Select the Schedule Tab
Right Click In the Schedule Tab Calendar Area
Select to Click on the First Phase of the Plan
Hold the Shift Key Down + Select the Last Resource Line of the Plan to Highlight ALL Lines
Select Input Capture Window
